This paper is about natural language processing using deep learning, which is a common topic in the computer science sub-category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper specifically focuses on the effectiveness of neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of neural networks, which could also be relevant to the sub-categories of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses empirical evidence to demonstrate the effectiveness of neural networks, which could also be relevant to the sub-category of "Computational Complexity" (cs.CC).
